        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 8:34PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 834 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Happy Camp Campground, or 24 miles northwest of Lakeview, moving
northwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Happy Camp Campground, Cox Pass, Lookout Rock Trailhead, Campbell And
Dead Horse Lakes, North Fork Sprague River Trailhead, Dairy Point
Campground, and Lee Thomas Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
